Charli XCX returns with “SS26,” a new single and visual directed by @torso.solutions that transforms the fashion industry into an apocalyptic runway. Set against the backdrop of backstage chaos, casting-call theatrics, and luxury excess, the project blurs the line between satire and reality: capturing what Charli describes as “a runway that goes straight to hell.”
The release continues her ongoing exploration of celebrity, image, and cultural performance, pairing distorted guitars and apathetic lyricism with a cast of fashion industry figures and underground creatives.
“Nothing’s gonna save us, not music fashion or film,” Charli writes, while simultaneously embracing the spectacle of it all - “Yeah I think I’ll be alright if I look good in the clothes.” “SS26” positions fashion not as escapism, but as part of the collapse itself; glamorous, self-aware, and impossible to look away from.
Featuring: Abra, Anthony Vaccarello, Baby Deva, Benjamin Barron, Bror August Vestbø, Carine Roitfeld, Ceval, Dan Sablon, David Siwicki, Debra Shaw, Farida Khelfa, Gian Gisiger, Lucien Pagès, Lyas, Michel Gaubert, Nhu Duong, Patrik Sandberg, Ryan Aguilar, Victoria Sekrier, Zac Ching, Loïc Prigent
