@vans has opened a new flagship in the heart of Brera, bringing Milan’s local creative community under one roof. The new concept stocks names like NOVE25 and Rhizome alongside special BAPE, UNDERCOVER, and Vans Milan capsules.⁠
⁠
Beyond sneakers and apparel, there’s vinyl, books, magazines, jewelry, fragrances, and plenty of skate gear. Basically, a Vans store worth hanging around in. Will you be stopping by?

@rkive of @bts.bighitofficial wore a small independent label on one of the world’s biggest stages. His custom World Cup halftime look came from @marie.lueder , the German-founded, Berlin Fashion Week regular, and was adapted from its AW26 Ghosts of My Life collection.⁠
⁠
LUEDER is known for turning sportswear, tailoring, and medieval armor into what it calls “Mental Armour.” Going from an emerging European runway label to dressing BTS in front of the world is a pretty major leap.

@oakley is releasing an ultra-rare prototype of its X-Metal MUZM Juliet on July 24, exclusively at five stores worldwide.⁠
⁠
Built from 25 parts using Oakley’s titanium 3D-printing technology, each pair comes engraved with its own serial number and sealed in special packaging. In Japan, getting one requires winning a lottery at Oakley Shibuya. Safe to say, these won’t be easy to find.

@lilbieber fans take two things very seriously: Justin Bieber and his brand.
For fans and fashion aficionados alike, Bieber is redefining what a celebrity brand can be for Gen Z. We spoke with fans waiting outside the @skylrk pop-up to hear their expectations for the brand, what they’re most excited to shop, and just how long they’re willing to stand in line for Justin Bieber and his clothes.
📷: @byeemj , @konquestky , Beatriz Ceita

@TheOdysseyMovie di #ChristopherNolan - primo lungometraggio girato interamente in IMAX 70 mm -, trasforma il poema omerico in un'interrogazione sulle responsabilità morali e politiche del presente. Il suo #Ulisse, interpretato da #MattDamon, non è l'eroe trionfante della tradizione, ma un uomo perseguitato dal ricordo della guerra di Troia e dalle conseguenze del cavallo da lui stesso ideato. Privato della sua aura divina, vulnerabile e profondamente umano, torna a Itaca sentendosi non un vincitore, ma uno sconfitto. Sostenuta dalla fotografia di #HoyteVanHoytema e dal soundtrack di @LudwigGoransson, l'Odissea di Nolan recupera la struttura della tragedia, dove l'eccellenza dell'eroe coincide con la causa della sua rovina, e riflette sull'incapacità del potere odierno di preservare l'ordine e la pace. Continua a leggere l'articolo a cura di @AlessandroViapiana_ al link in bio.
Photo: Universal Pictures
